This workshop consists of two parts;

First, a basic introduction to quantum networks. Here, I will introduce the basic building blocks of a quantum internet: quantum bits (qubits), entanglement, and quantum repeaters. I will then explain quantum mechanical phenomena enable greater security for communication and how entanglement is a fundamentally new resource for distributed tasks and computation.

Secondly, to illustrate these concepts, I will take the audience through an implementation of a simple Quantum Key Distribution (QKD) application whereby Alice and Bob create a quantum-secured secret key which they can use to encrypt their communication. This will be done in Python using the tools available on the Quantum Network Explorer.
